                <h1>Cheița Gorge</h1>
                <p>Cheița Gorge is a stunning gorge located in Romania's Bucegi Mountains, known for its dramatic limestone cliffs, crystal-clear streams, and lush vegetation. This natural wonder offers visitors breathtaking scenery and exciting hiking opportunities through its narrow passages and along its rushing waters.</p>
                <p>Cheița Gorge is a path where stone and water shape the journey. The river has carved its way through the limestone, leaving behind walls that rise tall and narrow, guarding the trail in silence. Roots cling to the rock, trees bend overhead, and the sound of rushing water follows every step. At times, the way squeezes tight between stone, at others it opens to reveal the forest light. To walk through Cheița Gorge is to follow the river’s secret, a passage where nature’s strength and beauty stand side by side.</p>
